article.headline: Kent State 74, New Hampshire 47
article.story: KENT, Ohio (AP) -- Armon Gates scored 16 points Saturday night to lead Kent State to a 74-47 win over New Hampshire in the championship game of the Kent State Classic. Ahead 29-20 at halftime, Kent (7-5) used a 28-8 run to open the second half, shooting 60 percent from the field. Mike Scott scored 12 points and Haminn Quaintance added 11 for Kent, which has won two straight. Jermaine Anderson led New Hampshire (3-9) with 13 points and Janev Blagoj added 10 points and 11 rebounds. Kent scored 18 points off 22 turnovers by the Wildcats, who shot just 35 percent for the game.
